<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!DOCTYPE en-export SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/evernote-export2.dtd"><en-export export-date="20130826T134752Z" application="Evernote/Windows" version="4.x"><note><title>Rackspace #320</title><content><![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note style="background: #cccccc;font-family: 'Helvetica Neue',  Helvetica, Arial, 'Liberation Sans', FreeSans, sans-serif;color: #585957;font-size: 14px;line-height: 1.3;"><?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>            <!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd">            <en-note style="word-wrap: break-word; -webkit-nbsp-mode: space; -webkit-line-break: after-white-space;">            Core V2  10-18-2012<BR/><BR/>Delete old tickets - improves performance and speeds things up for Core.<BR/><BR/>Archival ?  Not so much now...  ???<BR/><BR/>Problem is PostgresSQL...   What about Amazon DynamoDB ?  Oops - can't switch engines. Doh !!!<BR/><BR/>Relational don't scale !!!<BR/><BR/>Oracle can shard but still each shard has an upper limit that's not high enough...<BR/><BR/>Realtime SalesForce - Proxy --> memcache --> SalesForce APEX !!!<BR/><BR/>Smart cache... background updates to SaleForce - updates flow through the cache NOT SalesForce.<BR/><BR/>Core V2 is SOA - break apart services and recode those parts as SOA.<BR/><BR/><BR/><BR/>#rackspace  #core #cognizant #rearchitecture              </en-note></en-note>]]></content><created>20121018T062730Z</created><updated>19700101T052640Z</updated><tag>rackspace</tag><tag>core</tag><tag>cognizant</tag><tag>rearchitecture</tag></note></en-export>
